 Staff members check an e-bus produced by Yutong before the departure ceremony of Yutong electric vehicles to Qatar in Zhengzhou, central China's Henan Province, Dec. 17, 2021. The departure ceremony of Yutong electric vehicles to Qatar was held in Zhengzhou on Friday. A total of 741 electric vehicles will be transported by sea to Qatar for the Qatar FIFA World Cup 2022. (Xinhua/Li Jianan)  A staff member checks an e-bus produced by Yutong before the departure ceremony of Yutong electric vehicles to Qatar in Zhengzhou, central China's Henan Province, Dec. 17, 2021. The departure ceremony of Yutong electric vehicles to Qatar was held in Zhengzhou on Friday. A total of 741 electric vehicles will be transported by sea to Qatar for the Qatar FIFA World Cup 2022. (Xinhua/Li Jianan)  An e-bus produced by Yutong comes out from a workshop after the departure ceremony of Yutong electric vehicles to Qatar in Zhengzhou, central China's Henan Province, Dec. 17, 2021. The departure ceremony of Yutong electric vehicles to Qatar was held in Zhengzhou on Friday. A total of 741 electric vehicles will be transported by sea to Qatar for the Qatar FIFA World Cup 2022. (Xinhua/Li Jianan)  An e-bus produced by Yutong is seen during the departure ceremony of Yutong electric vehicles to Qatar in Zhengzhou, central China's Henan Province, Dec. 17, 2021. The departure ceremony of Yutong electric vehicles to Qatar was held in Zhengzhou on Friday. A total of 741 electric vehicles will be transported by sea to Qatar for the Qatar FIFA World Cup 2022. (Xinhua/Li Jianan)  An e-bus produced by Yutong is seen during the departure ceremony of Yutong electric vehicles to Qatar in Zhengzhou, central China's Henan Province, Dec. 17, 2021. The departure ceremony of Yutong electric vehicles to Qatar was held in Zhengzhou on Friday. A total of 741 electric vehicles will be transported by sea to Qatar for the Qatar FIFA World Cup 2022. (Xinhua/Li Jianan)